    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2017-10-04</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2019-08-23T18:31:04Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><b>Empower Act of 2017</b></p> <p>This bill modifies the system for the public financing&nbsp;of presidential elections, including by&nbsp;(1) providing for 600% matching funds for campaign contributions&nbsp;that are&nbsp;smaller contributions; and (2) requiring a candidate, as a condition of eligibility for public financing,&nbsp;to agree&nbsp;not to&nbsp;accept certain bundled contributions or contributions of more than $1,000 from any person. The bill also modifies other election-related provisions, such as by&nbsp;expanding disclosure requirements related to certain bundled contributions made to presidential campaigns.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
